'''Keenen Ivory Desuma Wayans''' (born June 8, 1958)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pbs.org/weta/finding-your-roots/about/meet-our-guests/keenan-ivory-wayans|title=Keenen Ivory Wayans|access-date=August 17, 2021|publisher=PBS}}</ref> is an American actor, comedian, director and filmmaker. He is a member of the [[Wayans family]] of entertainers. Wayans first came to prominence as the host and creator of the 1990–1994 [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] sketch comedy series ''[[In Living Color]]''. He has produced, directed or written several films, starting with ''[[Hollywood Shuffle]]'', which he cowrote, in 1987. Most of his films have included him and one or more of his siblings in the cast.

One of these films, ''[[Scary Movie]]'' (2000), which Wayans directed, was the highest-grossing movie directed by an African American until it was surpassed by [[Tim Story]]'s ''[[Fantastic Four (2005 film)|Fantastic Four]]'' in 2005. From 1997 to 1998, he hosted the talk show ''[[The Keenen Ivory Wayans Show]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title= Will 'Hip' Equal 'Hit'? |work= [[Los Angeles Times]]|date=August 3, 1997|url= https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1997-aug-03-ca-18836-story.html|access-date=2011-11-06|first=Greg|last=Braxton}}</ref> In 2014, he was a judge for the eighth season of ''[[Last Comic Standing]]''.

==Life and career==
Wayans was born in [[Harlem]], New York City, son of Howell Stouten Wayans, a supermarket manager, and his wife Elvira Alethia (Green), a homemaker and social worker.<ref>Stated on ''[[Finding Your Roots]]'', January 19, 2016, PBS</ref> He is the second of ten children.<ref name=":0" /> Genealogical TV show ''[[Finding Your Roots]]'' revealed that his paternal line traced back to [[Madagascar]].<ref name=":0">{{cite web |last1=Johnson |first1=Martin |title=Finding Your Roots: Shonda Rhimes, Maya Rudolph and Keenen Ivory Wayans Learn Shocking Facts About Their Families |url=https://www.theroot.com/finding-your-roots-shonda-rhimes-maya-rudolph-and-kee-1790853934 |website=The Root |date=January 18, 2016 |publisher=G/O Media Inc. |access-date=23 February 2022 |language=en-us}}</ref> His father was a devout [[Jehovah's Witness]].<ref>{{cite magazine| url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,997920,00.html | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071104105953/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,997920,00.html | url-status=dead | archive-date=November 4, 2007 | magazine=Time | title=Marlon Wayans | first=Joel | last=Stein | date=September 11, 2000}}</ref><ref>[http://www.themoviechicks.com/mid2004/mctladykillers.html The Movie Chicks – Interview – Marlon Wayans<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The family later moved to  Manhattan's [[Fulton Houses|Fulton]] housing projects,<ref name= ready>{{cite news |title= Is prime time ready for rudeness? Fox's new comedy 'In Living Color' will offend some, tickle others |work= The San Diego Union |date= April 13, 1990 |first= Robert P. |last= Laurence |url= http://infoweb.newsbank.com/iw-search/we/InfoWeb?p_product=AWNB&p_theme=aggregated5&p_action=doc&p_docid=1178BA5E348E4AB6&p_docnum=845&p_queryname=3 |page= E1 }}</ref> where he primarily grew up. He attended [[Seward Park High School]] during his teenage years, and attended [[Tuskegee University]] on an engineering scholarship.<ref name= ready/> He entertained his friends at college with made-up stories about life in New York.<ref name= laughing>{{cite news |title= Laughing with 'Living Color' |work= USA Today |date= April 13, 1990 |first= Mike |last= Hughes |url= http://infoweb.newsbank.com/iw-search/we/InfoWeb?p_product=AWNB&p_theme=aggregated5&p_action=doc&p_docid=128129675C049B80&p_docnum=850&p_queryname=3 }}</ref> One semester befor

