[[Virat Kohli]] is an Indian [[cricket|cricketer]] and a former captain of the [[Indian national cricket team]]. A right-handed top-order batsman, he has made 82 [[Century (cricket)|centuries]] in international cricket—30 in [[Test cricket]], 51 in [[One Day International]]s (ODIs) and 1 in [[Twenty20 International]]s (T20Is). However [[Sachin Tendulkar]] remains to have the most international centuries in the sport.{{efn|Kohli is second on the all-time list.<ref
name="mostcenturies">{{cite web|title=Records / Combined Test, ODI and T20I records / Batting records / Most hundreds in a career|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/records/284175.html |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |access-date=15 January 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121004152723/http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/records/284175.html |archive-date=4 October 2012 }}</ref>}}

Kohli made his debut against [[Sri Lanka national cricket team|Sri Lanka]] in August 2008,<ref name=ESPNcricinfo1>{{cite web|title=Virat Kohli |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/india/content/player/253802.html |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |access-date=26 February 2014 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140225193217/http://www.espncricinfo.com/india/content/player/253802.html |archive-date=25 February 2014 }}</ref> and scored his first century the following year when he made 107 against the same team at [[Eden Gardens]], [[Kolkata]]. His 86-ball 133 [[Not out (cricket)|not out]] against Sri Lanka in February 2012 led [[India national cricket team|India]] to the second highest run-chase by any team in Australia.{{efn|India reached their target of 321 runs in 36.4 overs.<ref>{{cite web|last=Talya |first=Siddhartha |title=Dazzling Kohli ton keeps India alive |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/commonwealth-bank-series-2012/content/story/555498.html |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |access-date=26 February 2014 |date=28 February 2012 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140304075632/http://www.espncricinfo.com/commonwealth-bank-series-2012/content/story/555498.html |archive-date=4 March 2014
}}</ref>}}{{Sfn|Memon|Rao|2013|loc=section 5}}<ref>{{cite web|last=Hogan |first=Jesse |title=Commonwealth Bank Series, 2011–12 |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/wisdenalmanack/content/story/699415.html |work=[[Wisden Cricketers' Almanack]] |date=11 December 2013 |publisher=reprinted by ESPNcricinfo |access-date=26 February 2014 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140314215148/http://www.espncricinfo.com/wisdenalmanack/content/story/699415.html |archive-date=14 March 2014 }}</ref> Former Australian cricketer [[Dean Jones (cricketer)|Dean Jones]] described the innings as "One of the greatest ODI knocks of all time!".<ref>{{cite news |title=Kohli earns Jones' praise |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120303/jsp/sports/story_15207013.jsp#.Uw4q-B2L-Nw |access-date=26 February 2014 |newspaper=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)|The Telegraph]] |date=3 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303055535/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120303/jsp/sports/story_15207013.jsp#.Uw4q-B2L-Nw |archive-date=3 March 2014 }}</ref> Kohli's highest score of 183 came against [[Pakistan national cricket team|Pakistan]] during the [[Asia Cup 2012|2012 Asia Cup]]; India successfully chased a target of 330 set by Pakistan and Kohli was adjudged [[man of the match]]. Following that, he made his first century as a captain while playing against the [[2013 West Indies Tri-Series|West Indies in the 2013 Triangular Series]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kohli hits first century as India ODI captain |url=http://www.rediff.com/cricket/report/slide-show-1-west-indies-tri-series-2013-stats-highlights-kohli-hits-first-century-as-india-captain/20130706.htm |work=[[Rediff.com]] |date=6 July 2013 |access-date=13 March 2014 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313223048/http://www.rediff.com/cricket/report/slide-show-1-west-indies-tri-series-2013-stats-highlights-kohli-hits-first-century-as-india-captain/20130706.htm |archive-date=13 March 2014 }}</ref> In the bilateral series against [[Australia national cricket team|Australia]] in October 2013, Kohli made two centuries in successful run-chases. The first of the two, 100 not out, was scored off 52 balls and remains the fastest ODI century by an Indian.<ref name=ODItons>{{cite web|title=Records / One-Day Internationals / Batting records / Fastest hundreds |url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/records/211608.html |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |access-date=26 February 2013 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107213559/http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/records/211608.html

